1
00:00:04,381 --> 00:00:06,861
- Attention, everyone,
a bomb was just found on a bus

2
00:00:06,905 --> 00:00:07,775
in Downtown Brooklyn.

3
00:00:07,819 --> 00:00:09,299
- Oh, my God, a bomb on a bus.

4
00:00:09,342 --> 00:00:11,257
It's a "Speed"?
I get to work a "Speed"?

5
00:00:11,301 --> 00:00:12,824
- That sentence is nonsensical.

6
00:00:12,867 --> 00:00:13,955
One can work with speed,

7
00:00:13,999 --> 00:00:15,566
but one certainly
cannot work a speed.

8
00:00:15,609 --> 00:00:17,568
- "Speed" is a movie.
I won't let you ruin this!

9
00:00:17,611 --> 00:00:19,004
- Really never seen
"Speed," sir?

10
00:00:19,047 --> 00:00:20,397
Keanu Reeves, Sandy Bullock,

11
00:00:20,440 --> 00:00:22,007
Jeff Daniels at the height
of his sexual powers?

12
00:00:22,050 --> 00:00:23,226
- Can we please just focus!

13
00:00:23,269 --> 00:00:24,575
The bomb could go off
at any moment.

14
00:00:24,618 --> 00:00:27,360
- Actually, it can't.
It's already been defused.

15
00:00:27,404 --> 00:00:29,101
- Oh, well, there's still
a bomber on the loose.

16
00:00:29,144 --> 00:00:30,363
You can't ruin this!

17
00:00:30,407 --> 00:00:31,451
All right,
tell me about the bus.

18
00:00:31,495 --> 00:00:32,583
Was it headed
to the courthouse?

19
00:00:32,626 --> 00:00:35,150
- It wasn't an MTA bus.
It was that.

20
00:00:35,194 --> 00:00:36,456
A "Marvelous Mrs. Maisel"
tour bus.

21
00:00:36,500 --> 00:00:38,066
- No, you're not ruining this!

22
00:00:38,110 --> 00:00:39,372
Has anyone heard
from the bomber?

23
00:00:39,416 --> 00:00:40,765
Has he made any demands?

24
00:00:40,808 --> 00:00:43,333
- Whoa, whoa, whoa.
Special Agent Feingold, FBI.

25
00:00:43,376 --> 00:00:45,291
This is our case.
You're not a part of it.

26
00:00:45,335 --> 00:00:47,815
- Oh, man!
You ruined it!

27
00:00:50,818 --> 00:00:57,782
♪

28
00:01:07,792 --> 00:01:09,881
Agent Feingold, our guys
were on the scene first.

29
00:01:09,924 --> 00:01:11,274
We're not gonna
let you take the case.

30
00:01:11,317 --> 00:01:12,405
Tell him, sir.

31
00:01:12,449 --> 00:01:13,580
- We're letting you
take the case.

32
00:01:13,624 --> 00:01:15,147
- What?
But I said that so cool!

33
00:01:15,190 --> 00:01:16,888
- They're the feds.
They have jurisdiction.

34
00:01:16,931 --> 00:01:18,759
Agent Feingold, call me
if you need anything.

35
00:01:18,803 --> 00:01:20,413
- Sorry, guy,
guess you're just gonna have

36
00:01:20,457 --> 00:01:22,502
to let the big boys handle it.
- Please just let us help you.

37
00:01:22,546 --> 00:01:23,982
This is
an all-hands-on-deck situation.

38
00:01:24,025 --> 00:01:26,463
I could be a good resource.
Here, watch this.

39
00:01:26,506 --> 00:01:28,421
What's up, Officer Marzipan?
- Oh, hey.

40
00:01:28,465 --> 00:01:29,727
- You're gonna want
that kind of shorthand

41
00:01:29,770 --> 00:01:31,337
with Marzipan if you
want to catch this guy.

42
00:01:31,381 --> 00:01:32,643
- We don't need
all hands on deck.

43
00:01:32,686 --> 00:01:34,645
The bomb was rigged
with a chintzy $4 watch

44
00:01:34,688 --> 00:01:36,516
set to explode at 12:00 a.m.
- Midnight?

45
00:01:36,560 --> 00:01:38,126
But there wouldn't be
anybody on it.

46
00:01:38,170 --> 00:01:39,780
- Yeah, the idiot clearly meant
to set it for noon.

47
00:01:39,824 --> 00:01:41,434
We're not dealing
with a mastermind here.

48
00:01:41,478 --> 00:01:42,827
I'm sure there's prints
all over the place

49
00:01:42,870 --> 00:01:44,481
- I don't know—I've just got
a gut feeling

50
00:01:44,524 --> 00:01:46,657
there's more to this.
- Oh, a gut feeling?

51
00:01:46,700 --> 00:01:48,920
You know what your gut tells
you to do most of the time?

52
00:01:48,963 --> 00:01:50,269
Take a dump.

53
00:01:50,313 --> 00:01:52,967
And you just took a big one
all over yourself.

54
00:01:56,014 --> 00:01:57,624
- Okay, well, I don't have
a comeback for that,

55
00:01:57,668 --> 00:01:59,626
so I'm just gonna go.

56
00:01:59,670 --> 00:02:01,889
Agent Feingold.

57
00:02:04,196 --> 00:02:07,199
- Scully, it's our favorite
time of year.

58
00:02:07,242 --> 00:02:09,984
Cagney and Lacey's
annual school candy drive!

59
00:02:10,028 --> 00:02:11,464
I took the liberty
of duplicating

60
00:02:11,508 --> 00:02:12,987
your order from last year.

61
00:02:13,031 --> 00:02:14,685
Simply sign at the X,
and I'll get it placed for you.

62
00:02:14,728 --> 00:02:16,469
- Oh, about that, I don't know

63
00:02:16,513 --> 00:02:18,297
if I'm gonna buy anything
from you this year.

64
00:02:18,341 --> 00:02:19,690
- What?

65
00:02:19,733 --> 00:02:22,388
But we've been in business
together since pre-K.

66
00:02:22,432 --> 00:02:24,085
- I know,
but there's someone else.

67
00:02:24,129 --> 00:02:25,260
- Someone else?

68
00:02:25,304 --> 00:02:26,610
- It's not you.
It's me.

69
00:02:26,653 --> 00:02:28,002
My taste in candy changed.

70
00:02:28,046 --> 00:02:30,178
- Look, everyone goes
through rough patches,

71
00:02:30,222 --> 00:02:31,615
but we can't give up.

72
00:02:31,658 --> 00:02:33,486
You owe it to Cagney and Lacey.

73
00:02:33,530 --> 00:02:35,183
- Please don't bring
the kids into this.

74
00:02:35,227 --> 00:02:37,403
- The kids are a part of it
whether you like it or not.

75
00:02:37,447 --> 00:02:39,710
Who are you buying from?
Tell me, now!

76
00:02:39,753 --> 00:02:41,929
- The other man is me.

77
00:02:41,973 --> 00:02:45,977
Nikolaj is selling candy
this year, too.

78
00:02:46,020 --> 00:02:48,806
- You're cheating on me
with Boyle?

79
00:02:48,849 --> 00:02:51,504
- Oh, there she is,
my archnemesis.

80
00:02:51,548 --> 00:02:52,723
- You're a cop, O'Sullivan.

81
00:02:52,766 --> 00:02:54,333
shouldn't your archnemesis
be a criminal?

82
00:02:54,377 --> 00:02:57,380
- No.
- Okay, what do you want?

83
00:02:57,423 --> 00:02:58,772
- Well, I came here
to reach a truce

84
00:02:58,816 --> 00:03:00,731
with you over your
pilot program that persecutes

85
00:03:00,774 --> 00:03:02,733
the uniformed officers
in my union.

86
00:03:02,776 --> 00:03:04,909
- Its aim is to reduce
instances in which armed cops

87
00:03:04,952 --> 00:03:07,041
are needlessly interacting
with civilians.

88
00:03:07,085 --> 00:03:10,044
It could save lives and restore
trust with the community.

89
00:03:10,088 --> 00:03:11,524
- That's persecution,
plain and simple.

90
00:03:11,568 --> 00:03:13,004
But I don't want
to fight with you.

91
00:03:13,047 --> 00:03:15,049
I'd rather be civilized
and reach some common ground

92
00:03:15,093 --> 00:03:16,790
over a drink.
- It's the middle of the day.

93
00:03:16,834 --> 00:03:19,053
- Well, that's how business
gets done in the real world.

94
00:03:19,097 --> 00:03:20,751
- Look, I'm not changing
the pilot program.

95
00:03:20,794 --> 00:03:22,448
- Okay, have it your way,

96
00:03:22,492 --> 00:03:25,451
but I got to say,
you're going to be sorry.

97
00:03:25,495 --> 00:03:26,931
- Are you threatening me?

98
00:03:26,974 --> 00:03:28,889
- No, I'm informing you
that I hold a lot of power,

99
00:03:28,933 --> 00:03:30,543
and unless you're willing
to play ball with me,

100
00:03:30,587 --> 00:03:32,415
I will wield said power
against you.

101
00:03:32,458 --> 00:03:33,807
Again, not a threat,

102
00:03:33,851 --> 00:03:35,940
but go ahead
and change your mind, or else.

103
00:03:35,983 --> 00:03:37,855
All the best.

104
00:03:37,898 --> 00:03:39,900
- So you lost a "Speed."
That sucks.

105
00:03:39,944 --> 00:03:41,728
At least you didn't have
a "Sister Act" taken from you.

106
00:03:41,772 --> 00:03:42,903
- Bracco confessed.

107
00:03:42,947 --> 00:03:44,165
The undercover operation
is over.

108
00:03:44,209 --> 00:03:45,993
- But I just got a spot
in the choir.

109
00:03:46,037 --> 00:03:47,560
- Wait, is that the real reason
you left the force?

110
00:03:47,604 --> 00:03:48,779
- It didn't help.
- Right.

111
00:03:48,822 --> 00:03:50,302
Look, I don't care
that I lost a "Speed."

112
00:03:50,345 --> 00:03:52,565
I care that the FBI is not
taking the case seriously.

113
00:03:52,609 --> 00:03:54,175
They think the bomber
is just some idiot,

114
00:03:54,219 --> 00:03:55,612
but what if he's not an idiot?

115
00:03:55,655 --> 00:03:58,049
What if he wanted it
to go off at midnight?

116
00:03:58,092 --> 00:03:59,746
Oh, my God.

117
00:03:59,790 --> 00:04:01,487
He wanted it
to go off at midnight.

118
00:04:01,531 --> 00:04:02,662
- Why? Wouldn't it just be

119
00:04:02,706 --> 00:04:03,924
an empty parking lot
with nobody in it?

120
00:04:03,968 --> 00:04:05,448
- Yeah, but there could be
a target there,

121
00:04:05,491 --> 00:04:06,971
which he would try
to hit again.

122
00:04:07,014 --> 00:04:08,494
There's gonna be a second bomb,
just like in "Speed"!

123
00:04:08,538 --> 00:04:10,191
I've got
a "Speed" again!

124
00:04:10,235 --> 00:04:11,671
- I thought you said you didn't
care about it being a "Speed."

125
00:04:11,715 --> 00:04:12,890
- Of course, I care about it
being a "Speed"!

126
00:04:12,933 --> 00:04:15,066
That's all I care about!
I've got to go!

127
00:04:15,109 --> 00:04:17,503
- You owe me money for this.
- Good one, Rosa!

128
00:04:20,550 --> 00:04:24,641
♪

129
00:04:24,684 --> 00:04:26,033
Hi.
- Hey.

130
00:04:26,077 --> 00:04:27,382
I just got home.
Where are you?

131
00:04:27,426 --> 00:04:28,514
- Sorry,
I'm checking out the lot

132
00:04:28,558 --> 00:04:29,602
where the bus parks at night.

133
00:04:29,646 --> 00:04:31,561
- Ugh,
but Holt told you not to.

134
00:04:31,604 --> 00:04:32,953
He's gonna be pissed
when he finds out.

135
00:04:32,997 --> 00:04:34,433
- Not when I bust the bomber.

136
00:04:34,477 --> 00:04:35,608
Marzipan gave me
the lot's address.

137
00:04:35,652 --> 00:04:36,783
He's actually helping me out

138
00:04:36,827 --> 00:04:38,045
because of our
intimate shorthand.

139
00:04:38,089 --> 00:04:40,091
- You know,
Marzipan's kind of a bad dude.

140
00:04:40,134 --> 00:04:41,701
We're desperately
trying to fire him.

141
00:04:41,745 --> 00:04:42,920
- No, I did not know that!

142
00:04:42,963 --> 00:04:44,182
Why didn't anyone tell me that

143
00:04:44,225 --> 00:04:45,705
before I pretended
to be friends with him?

144
00:04:45,749 --> 00:04:47,141
Well, looky here.

145
00:04:47,185 --> 00:04:49,143
- What?
- Guess what's next to the lot.

146
00:04:49,187 --> 00:04:51,450
An IRS building.
That has to be the target.

147
00:04:51,494 --> 00:04:53,147
- Jake,
you should call the feds.

148
00:04:53,191 --> 00:04:55,323
- No, they won't even care.
I need more proof.

149
00:04:55,367 --> 00:04:57,630
♪

150
00:04:57,674 --> 00:05:00,459
I got to call you back.
Hey.

151
00:05:00,503 --> 00:05:02,679
- Hey.
- NYPD.

152
00:05:02,722 --> 00:05:04,898
Mind if I ask you
a couple of questions?

153
00:05:06,465 --> 00:05:08,380
Wait, no, stop!
Ugh.

154
00:05:11,688 --> 00:05:15,996
♪

155
00:05:16,040 --> 00:05:17,824
Hey, there.

156
00:05:19,696 --> 00:05:22,002
- Uh-oh, I know that strut.

157
00:05:22,046 --> 00:05:23,656
Little hip swing,
playful butt bounce—

158
00:05:23,700 --> 00:05:24,962
somebody made a collar!

159
00:05:25,005 --> 00:05:26,790
- Not loving you talking
about my butt bounce,

160
00:05:26,833 --> 00:05:30,010
but, also, hell, yeah,
someone collared a big dog!

161
00:05:30,054 --> 00:05:31,446
- Woof, woof!

162
00:05:31,490 --> 00:05:33,057
- Peralta, you made an arrest
in the bus bombing?

163
00:05:33,100 --> 00:05:35,015
- Yes, look, I know
that I was told to back off,

164
00:05:35,059 --> 00:05:36,669
but something
just didn't sit right,

165
00:05:36,713 --> 00:05:38,932
so I went back up there,
and I caught the guy.

166
00:05:38,976 --> 00:05:41,152
He was snooping around.
Now, he's not talking yet—

167
00:05:41,195 --> 00:05:43,589
- Because he didn't do it.
- What?

168
00:05:43,633 --> 00:05:45,591
- The feds already
solved the case.

169
00:05:45,635 --> 00:05:47,158
There were prints on the bomb,

170
00:05:47,201 --> 00:05:49,116
which led to a suspect
who confessed immediately.

171
00:05:49,160 --> 00:05:50,683
- Well, why didn't anyone
tell me that?

172
00:05:50,727 --> 00:05:54,252
- 'Cause they didn't have to
because it's not your case.

173
00:05:54,295 --> 00:05:56,254
- So I arrested
an innocent person?

174
00:05:56,297 --> 00:05:57,385
- Yes.

175
00:05:57,429 --> 00:05:59,605
- Oh...

176
00:05:59,649 --> 00:06:01,912
that's not okay.

177
00:06:01,955 --> 00:06:03,261
Uncool, uncool, uncool, uncool,

178
00:06:03,304 --> 00:06:05,089
uncool, uncool,
uncool, uncool, uncool.

179
00:06:05,132 --> 00:06:07,308
- Are you saying
cool or uncool?

180
00:06:07,352 --> 00:06:09,920
- Uncool. It's just hard to say
it fast, but this is bad!

181
00:06:12,618 --> 00:06:14,751
- Peralta, we need to talk.
- I know.

182
00:06:14,794 --> 00:06:16,448
You're not mad.
You're just disappointed.

183
00:06:16,491 --> 00:06:18,058
- I'm actually
both mad and disappointed.

184
00:06:18,102 --> 00:06:19,364
- What?
You can't be both!

185
00:06:19,407 --> 00:06:21,540
You are either Mad Dad
or Sad Dad—pick a lane.

186
00:06:21,584 --> 00:06:23,629
All right, look, I know that
I brought in the wrong guy,

187
00:06:23,673 --> 00:06:25,283
but I'm telling you,
something doesn't add up,

188
00:06:25,326 --> 00:06:27,067
and for what it's worth,
I made sure he was let out

189
00:06:27,111 --> 00:06:28,416
as soon as I knew
what was going on.

190
00:06:28,460 --> 00:06:29,896
- He was in processing
for ten hours,

191
00:06:29,940 --> 00:06:32,377
which made him late for work,
which meant he got fired.

192
00:06:32,420 --> 00:06:34,161
He's suing you
and the department

193
00:06:34,205 --> 00:06:35,423
for wrongful arrest.

194
00:06:35,467 --> 00:06:36,642
I'm gonna have to suspend you.

195
00:06:36,686 --> 00:06:38,426
- Ugh, okay,
this is really bad,

196
00:06:38,470 --> 00:06:40,254
and I'm sor—
- Stop talking.

197
00:06:40,298 --> 00:06:41,429
What's going on here?

198
00:06:41,473 --> 00:06:42,517
Were you about
to say the S word?

199
00:06:42,561 --> 00:06:43,780
- The S word?
"Sorry"?

200
00:06:43,823 --> 00:06:45,608
- Oh, good God,
don't say it out loud, man!

201
00:06:45,651 --> 00:06:47,218
- Why are you here, O'Sullivan?

202
00:06:47,261 --> 00:06:49,089
Peralta isn't even
in the patrolman's union.

203
00:06:49,133 --> 00:06:50,830
- I'm here to protect Marzipan.

204
00:06:50,874 --> 00:06:52,571
He and Peralta
worked very closely together

205
00:06:52,615 --> 00:06:54,921
on this one.
- Seriously, Peralta, Marzipan?

206
00:06:54,965 --> 00:06:57,054
With all the open I.A.
investigations against him?

207
00:06:57,097 --> 00:06:58,272
- I've met him, like, one time.

208
00:06:58,316 --> 00:06:59,491
I don't even know
his first name.

209
00:06:59,534 --> 00:07:01,536
- His name is David.
David Duke Marzipan.

210
00:07:01,580 --> 00:07:03,016
- David Duke Marzipan?

211
00:07:03,060 --> 00:07:04,757
- Hey, don't you
go profiling him

212
00:07:04,801 --> 00:07:06,367
for what he
changed his name to.

213
00:07:06,411 --> 00:07:08,152
You can't judge a book
by its cover.

214
00:07:08,195 --> 00:07:10,023
- You can if it's written
by David Duke.

215
00:07:10,067 --> 00:07:11,677
- Look,
Peralta made a mistake—

216
00:07:11,721 --> 00:07:14,245
- Holy crap, you didn't use
the M word, did you?

217
00:07:14,288 --> 00:07:15,899
- No.
- Oh, thank God.

218
00:07:15,942 --> 00:07:17,291
Because the M word
is just about the worst thing

219
00:07:17,335 --> 00:07:18,423
you can say if you're a cop.

220
00:07:18,466 --> 00:07:20,381
Besides,
the real point here is,

221
00:07:20,425 --> 00:07:21,687
what was the perp doing

222
00:07:21,731 --> 00:07:23,602
snooping around
a bus lot at night?

223
00:07:23,646 --> 00:07:25,169
- The victim
cuts through that lot

224
00:07:25,212 --> 00:07:26,649
on his way home when it's open,

225
00:07:26,692 --> 00:07:28,433
and it was open because
Peralta picked the lock.

226
00:07:28,476 --> 00:07:30,130
- What a bunch of bunk.

227
00:07:30,174 --> 00:07:32,393
Why'd the perp run away unless
he was guilty of something?

228
00:07:32,437 --> 00:07:34,134
- Because he was
understandably scared

229
00:07:34,178 --> 00:07:35,353
of interacting with a cop.

230
00:07:35,396 --> 00:07:36,746
- I see—
well, that excuse hasn't worked

231
00:07:36,789 --> 00:07:38,748
in the last
15 cases against Marzipan,

232
00:07:38,791 --> 00:07:39,836
and I don't think
it'll work now.

233
00:07:39,879 --> 00:07:41,141
- 15?

234
00:07:41,185 --> 00:07:43,187
- Peralta, I can make
all of this disappear.

235
00:07:43,230 --> 00:07:44,667
That's what
the police union does.

236
00:07:44,710 --> 00:07:46,669
But you got
to play ball with me, son.

237
00:07:46,712 --> 00:07:48,018
What do you say?

238
00:07:48,061 --> 00:07:51,282
- Sir, can I speak with you
in private, please?

239
00:07:51,325 --> 00:07:52,762
I just had an epiphany.

240
00:07:52,805 --> 00:07:54,459
- That you're fallible
and you made an M word.

241
00:07:54,502 --> 00:07:58,376
- Absolutely not.
This whole thing is a setup!

242
00:07:58,419 --> 00:08:02,336
- ♪ Oh,
who could take a sunrise ♪

243
00:08:02,380 --> 00:08:05,644
