about one thing,

491
00:15:37,661 --> 00:15:40,229
it's getting cops off
without punishment.

492
00:15:40,272 --> 00:15:42,883
How dare you turn that
into something dirty?

493
00:15:42,927 --> 00:15:44,276
Shame on the both of you.

494
00:15:44,320 --> 00:15:45,973
- Oh, we got to call Jake.

495
00:15:48,672 --> 00:15:49,716
Where is he?

496
00:15:49,760 --> 00:15:52,502
♪

497
00:15:54,547 --> 00:15:55,505
- Got ya.

498
00:15:58,203 --> 00:16:00,510
- This is Captain Holt.

499
00:16:00,553 --> 00:16:03,295
- Oh, hello, Captain.
It's Amy Santiag-ago.

500
00:16:03,339 --> 00:16:04,818
- Sergeant, are you drunk?
- Oh, he thinks I'm drunk.

501
00:16:04,862 --> 00:16:06,820
What do I do?
- Uh, British accent.

502
00:16:06,864 --> 00:16:08,735
- Smart.
That'll fool him.

503
00:16:08,779 --> 00:16:10,389
Yes, sir, quite drunk.

504
00:16:10,433 --> 00:16:11,912
Wankered, really.

505
00:16:11,956 --> 00:16:13,653
- What did you learn?
Did O'Sullivan set up Peralta?

506
00:16:13,697 --> 00:16:14,828
- No, he didn't.

507
00:16:14,872 --> 00:16:16,308
Me husband
wasn't set up at all.

508
00:16:16,352 --> 00:16:19,311
He wasn't,
but me big problem now

509
00:16:19,355 --> 00:16:21,835
is that me husband
can't be reached by me telly.

510
00:16:21,879 --> 00:16:23,228
- Please stop
talking like that.

511
00:16:23,272 --> 00:16:24,316
- Okay.

512
00:16:24,360 --> 00:16:25,883
- Peralta wanted
to tail the victim.

513
00:16:25,926 --> 00:16:27,406
I forbade him,
but I bet he did it anyway.

514
00:16:27,450 --> 00:16:28,712
I'll text you the address.

515
00:16:28,755 --> 00:16:30,801
Oh.

516
00:16:30,844 --> 00:16:32,150
We got to stop Jake.

517
00:16:32,194 --> 00:16:33,891
- How?
We're too drunk to drive.

518
00:16:33,934 --> 00:16:35,632
- True, but we're not
too drunk to pedal.

519
00:16:37,286 --> 00:16:40,593
Jake, oh, thank God
we found you in time.

520
00:16:40,637 --> 00:16:42,682
- We?
- Me and Rosa, duh.

521
00:16:42,726 --> 00:16:45,119
- Rosa's not with you.
- Right.

522
00:16:45,163 --> 00:16:48,210
I lost her when she rode down
the stairs to the subway.

523
00:16:48,253 --> 00:16:50,951
It was so funny!

524
00:16:50,995 --> 00:16:53,215
- Okay, just shh,
'cause my guy is in there.

525
00:16:53,258 --> 00:16:54,738
- By the way,
I really like that hat.

526
00:16:54,781 --> 00:16:55,913
You look like a little narc.

527
00:16:55,956 --> 00:16:57,784
- And you enjoy that?
- Oh, yeah.

528
00:16:57,828 --> 00:16:59,482
- Okay.
- But that's not why I'm here.

529
00:16:59,525 --> 00:17:00,918
O'Sullivan didn't set you up.

530
00:17:00,961 --> 00:17:02,572
- Wait, what?
Are you sure?

531
00:17:02,615 --> 00:17:05,531
- Yeah, all O'Sullivan did was
mess with the vending machine

532
00:17:05,575 --> 00:17:07,011
and Scully's candy.

533
00:17:07,054 --> 00:17:08,317
That was his blackmail.

534
00:17:08,360 --> 00:17:11,798
- Okay.
Wow, okay, that's bad.

535
00:17:11,842 --> 00:17:13,060
That guy's innocent,
and I arrested him,

536
00:17:13,104 --> 00:17:14,279
and now I'm tailing him.

537
00:17:14,323 --> 00:17:16,586
- I know!
Let's just go "herm"!

538
00:17:16,629 --> 00:17:17,978
- Jake!
Jake!

539
00:17:18,022 --> 00:17:21,286
Hey, Jake, you're following
an innocent man!

540
00:17:27,597 --> 00:17:29,860
- Hey, man.

541
00:17:29,903 --> 00:17:33,255
What are you doing here?
What a weird coincidence.

542
00:17:33,298 --> 00:17:35,344
Do a British accent.

543
00:17:37,346 --> 00:17:39,609
- Hey, Lieutenant,
I think we should talk.

544
00:17:39,652 --> 00:17:41,045
How you doing?

545
00:17:41,088 --> 00:17:43,482
Oh, no, I'm so sorry.

546
00:17:43,526 --> 00:17:45,484
Sir, I want to apologize.

547
00:17:47,530 --> 00:17:48,922
- Okay, I have no idea
what you're saying.

548
00:17:48,966 --> 00:17:50,707
Look, I know
the union set us up,

549
00:17:50,750 --> 00:17:52,012
but we let it happen.

550
00:17:52,056 --> 00:17:54,014
Your friendship
means the world to me,

551
00:17:54,058 --> 00:17:55,712
and I would hate
for it to be destroyed

552
00:17:55,755 --> 00:17:57,714
by a competition
to sell more candy.

553
00:17:57,757 --> 00:17:59,411
- Me too.

554
00:17:59,455 --> 00:18:01,761
- You guys are selling candy?
There's nothing good here.

555
00:18:01,805 --> 00:18:03,981
Could one of you
ship to Brazil?

556
00:18:07,419 --> 00:18:10,683
- Oh!
You sneaky son of a bitch!

557
00:18:10,727 --> 00:18:13,469
- We're adding intimidation
to the charges against you.

558
00:18:13,512 --> 00:18:15,862
- I know, you're both mad
and disappointed.

559
00:18:15,906 --> 00:18:18,038
- I'm neither.
I'm displeased.

560
00:18:18,082 --> 00:18:19,518
- Is that worse?
- Yes.

561
00:18:19,562 --> 00:18:22,173
Of my 16 potential reactions,
only one is stronger,

562
00:18:22,216 --> 00:18:25,394
and you should be thankful
you've never seen me huffy.

563
00:18:25,437 --> 00:18:27,134
- Well, you have
every right to be.

564
00:18:27,178 --> 00:18:28,440
I know I messed up.

565
00:18:28,484 --> 00:18:29,876
I just never imagined myself
as someone

566
00:18:29,920 --> 00:18:31,138
who would make
a mistake like that,

567
00:18:31,182 --> 00:18:33,576
and then I just
made it worse, you know?

568
00:18:33,619 --> 00:18:35,534
- Whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa,
what are you doing?

569
00:18:35,578 --> 00:18:36,883
Learning a lesson?

570
00:18:36,927 --> 00:18:38,320
You don't have
any lessons to learn.

571
00:18:38,363 --> 00:18:39,886
You didn't do anything wrong.

572
00:18:39,930 --> 00:18:42,454
- What do you want, O'Sullivan?
- This is Mel Jenkins—

573
00:18:42,498 --> 00:18:45,152
city attorney in charge
of payoffs and bribes.

574
00:18:45,196 --> 00:18:47,241
- Uh, not my title.
I handle tort claims.

575
00:18:47,285 --> 00:18:49,418
- Whatever. Mel and I just had
ourselves a little chat

576
00:18:49,461 --> 00:18:51,463
over morning drinks.
- More drinks?

577
00:18:51,507 --> 00:18:53,857
- Relax, it was just
a couple of breakfast beers.

578
00:18:53,900 --> 00:18:56,338
So the department
is going to settle

579
00:18:56,381 --> 00:18:58,383
without admitting
any wrongdoing,

580
00:18:58,427 --> 00:19:01,299
and because the facts of the
case will remain unresolved,

581
00:19:01,343 --> 00:19:05,042
there will be no suspension
for Marzipan or Peralta

582
00:19:05,085 --> 00:19:06,348
- How's that possible?

583
00:19:06,391 --> 00:19:08,219
Peralta arrested
and harassed an innocent man.

584
00:19:08,262 --> 00:19:09,873
- Come on, now, these are cops.

585
00:19:09,916 --> 00:19:11,396
They got to make
split-second decisions

586
00:19:11,440 --> 00:19:13,442
in life-or-death situations,
and they can't be expected

587
00:19:13,485 --> 00:19:16,096
to get that 100% correct
every single time.

588
00:19:16,140 --> 00:19:17,837
- This was not
a life-or-death situation.

589
00:19:17,881 --> 00:19:19,404
- Sure, but next time
it might be.

590
00:19:19,448 --> 00:19:21,406
And how can this one
be expected to do his job

591
00:19:21,450 --> 00:19:25,192
when he knows that any
teeny-tiny lapse in judgment

592
00:19:25,236 --> 00:19:27,238
could end with you
branding him a dirty cop

593
00:19:27,281 --> 00:19:29,545
and ruining his life?

594
00:19:29,588 --> 00:19:31,503
- Oh, I've never seen
this face before.

595
00:19:31,547 --> 00:19:33,679
Wait, is that—

596
00:19:33,723 --> 00:19:35,942
- Yes, he's made me huffy.

597
00:19:35,986 --> 00:19:37,901
Do you know what happens
when you refuse

598
00:19:37,944 --> 00:19:39,511
to punish cops
for their mistakes,

599
00:19:39,555 --> 00:19:41,992
when police are treated
as a separate class

600
00:19:42,035 --> 00:19:43,559
of citizen above the law?

601
00:19:43,602 --> 00:19:46,388
It breeds a lack of trust
in the community,

602
00:19:46,431 --> 00:19:48,477
and that lack of trust
means people won't help us

603
00:19:48,520 --> 00:19:50,653
with our investigations
or testify

604
00:19:50,696 --> 00:19:53,046
or even call us
when they're in danger.

605
00:19:53,090 --> 00:19:54,874
It makes them more scared of us

606
00:19:54,918 --> 00:19:56,833
than of criminals
and gangsters.

607
00:19:56,876 --> 00:19:58,661
It makes them run
when we approach,

608
00:19:58,704 --> 00:20:00,402
even though
they've done nothing wrong.

609
00:20:00,445 --> 00:20:02,882
It makes the people
see us as the enemy,

610
00:20:02,926 --> 00:20:05,015
which leads
to more confrontation,

611
00:20:05,058 --> 00:20:06,930
more distrust.

612
00:20:06,973 --> 00:20:08,975
You wonder how Peralta
can do his job

613
00:20:09,019 --> 00:20:10,499
when he's held accountable
for his actions?

614
00:20:10,542 --> 00:20:15,286
I wonder how any of us
can do our job if he's not.

615
00:20:15,329 --> 00:20:18,550
- What a bunch of bunk.
The city's gonna settle.

616
00:20:18,594 --> 00:20:20,422
There are not gonna be
any suspensions.

617
00:20:20,465 --> 00:20:23,425
Take the win.
- Wait.

618
00:20:23,468 --> 00:20:25,862
What if I admit I made
an error and apologize?

619
00:20:25,905 --> 00:20:27,254
- He is speaking
hypothetically.

620
00:20:27,298 --> 00:20:29,126
You'll notice he never used
the S word

621
00:20:29,169 --> 00:20:30,432
and he never used the M word.

622
00:20:30,475 --> 00:20:31,911
- I'm sorry.
I made a mistake.

623
00:20:31,955 --> 00:20:33,130
- Holy [bleep]!

624
00:20:33,173 --> 00:20:34,392
Let the record show

625
00:20:34,436 --> 00:20:35,915
that he didn't say
anything specific.

626
00:20:35,959 --> 00:20:38,265
- I arrested a man without
a sufficient probable cause

627
00:20:38,309 --> 00:20:39,571
in a case I was removed from.

628
00:20:39,615 --> 00:20:41,399
- He has no idea
what he's talking about.

629
00:20:41,443 --> 00:20:43,270
- I then followed
my victim to his home...

630
00:20:43,314 --> 00:20:44,924
- Now's a good time
for us to leave.

631
00:20:44,968 --> 00:20:46,622
- In an act that could only
be seen as police intimidation.

632
00:20:46,665 --> 00:20:47,927
- La, la, la, la, la, la.

633
00:20:47,971 --> 00:20:49,538
- I take full responsibility
for my mistake,

634
00:20:49,581 --> 00:20:51,104
and I'm willing to say
as much in a court of law.

635
00:20:51,148 --> 00:20:52,410
- La, la, la, la, la, la.

636
00:20:52,454 --> 00:20:55,282
- And what's more,
I'm very, very sorry!

637
00:20:55,326 --> 00:20:58,068
- Yeah, he has to be suspended.

638
00:20:58,111 --> 00:20:59,591
I'm sorry.

639
00:20:59,635 --> 00:21:02,464
- Ah, don't you start.

640
00:21:02,507 --> 00:21:03,813
- Wow.

641
00:21:03,856 --> 00:21:05,510
That was amazing.
We beat him.

642
00:21:05,554 --> 00:21:07,947
I can't believe it
actually worked out okay.

643
00:21:07,991 --> 00:21:09,122
- You're suspended
for five months.

644
00:21:09,166 --> 00:21:11,211
- Right, I know.

645
00:21:11,255 --> 00:21:12,691
But I deserve it.

646
00:21:12,735 --> 00:21:15,781
And I learned a valuable lesson
from all this,

647
00:21:15,825 --> 00:21:17,783
so I'm counting it as a win.

648
00:21:17,827 --> 00:21:20,656
- I get that, Peralta,
but things will be a lot better

649
00:21:20,699 --> 00:21:22,440
when a man doesn't have
to lose his job

650
00:21:22,484 --> 00:21:25,312
for you to learn a lesson.

651
00:21:25,356 --> 00:21:27,750
- Yeah, fair enough.
Thank you, sir.

652
00:21:30,187 --> 00:21:31,580
It was crazy
when you got huffy.

653
00:21:31,623 --> 00:21:33,843
- I was so huffy.
- I got scared.

654
00:21:33,886 --> 00:21:35,192
- Wow.
- Yeah.

655
00:21:37,107 --> 00:21:39,196
- Not a doctor.
- Shh.

